  "prompt": "Which is the best camera phone performance under 10000?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, several smartphones under \u20b910,000 have gained a reputation for offering good camera performance. Here are a few notable options:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 50A**:\n   - Features a triple camera setup with a 50 MP primary sensor.\n   - Good low-light performance and decent overall image quality.\n   - Offers various camera features and modes.\n\n2. **Xiaomi Redmi 10**:\n   - Comes with a dual-camera setup, including a 50 MP main camera and a 2 MP depth sensor.\n   - Known for its dynamic range and color reproduction.\n   - Also includes features like night mode and AI enhancements.\n\n3. **Poco M4 Pro**:\n   - Offers a capable 64 MP main camera alongside an 8 MP ultra-wide lens.\n   - Good performance in different lighting conditions.\n   - Includes various camera modes like night and portrait.\n\n4. **Samsung Galaxy F22**:\n   - Features a 48 MP quad-camera setup.\n   - Known for its reliable camera performance, especially in good lighting.\n   - Samsung\u2019s camera software often provides good portraits and vibrant photos.\n\n5. **Infinix Hot 12 Pro**:\n   - Equipped with a 50 MP primary camera.\n   - Offers decent image quality for its price, particularly in well-lit conditions.\n\nWhen looking for a smartphone under \u20b910,000, it's essential to consider your specific needs (like video recording, low-light performance, or additional features). Always check for the latest user reviews and camera samples, as real-world performance can vary. Additionally, some of these models might go on sale or receive discounts, so keep an eye on pricing in your region.",
